description:
Wolverine and Gambit head to Japan to bail out Jubilee, only to be met by a group of deadly ninja assassins known as The Hand!

Wolverine and Gambit get Jubilee out of jail in Tokyo. The Hand attacks Wolverine due to Matsuo Tsurayaba. Sunfire helps the X-Men fight the Hand. Wolverine fights Cylla.
name: Thirty Slashes Over Tokio - or "Sayonara Yellow Brick Road"

description: Batman becomes a one-man invasion force in this single-issue story when Alfred is kidnapped and seemingly killed by terrorist drug smugglers!
name: Family

description:
Omega captures Drax, Pip, Gamora, and Moondragon and plans on using their powers to kill their old for Warlock!

Omega has successfully captured Drax, Pip, Gamora and Moondragon. He knows better than to use the gems on his person and instead uses their power through a machine. His plan- kill their old foe Adam Warlock.

Warlock has returned to where he left the Watch, only to find that they have already left. He contacts the possessor of the Reality Gem. He knows that they have been captured by the Omega and tells him where to find them. He suggests if he succeeds in rescuing them to give the gems to those more worthy.

The ship of Omega is orbiting the Earth. Warlock travels to the ship, but he is being watched. He uses stealth to easily defeat the lower members of the crew. He is met by Omega's second in command, who proves to be more than a worthy adversary. Warlock is plagued with self doubt, especially when he realizes that this is not the Omega that he is fighting.

After a long hard battle, Warlock comes out on top. He takes off his attacker's mask to reveal his old enemy from Counter Earth, Triax the Terrible. He now understands that the Omega can only be one person - the Man-Beast.
name: Old Foes

description: An Infinity War crossover.
name: Galactus, Go Home!

description:
Punisherroach debates with himself on whether to kill or do the women, eventually Elrod meets up with him. K'Cor asks Cerebus about his ascension. Astoria appears. Cerebus goes back to Po, who goes on with his story. Cirin gets Astoria's conditions for them to meet.

Also includes a sketch of Cerebus and Tyrant done by Dave and Steve Bissette to benefit the Comic Defense Legal Fund.
name: Mothers and Daughters 9 : Flight 9

description:
Jason gets out of the hospital. Headset gets out of the hospital. It's Mike Powell and Philippe Bazin’s funerals. 

Chris loses his cool at school when friends try to have him open up and share with them. Leaves school to become Darkhawk and stops a mugging to release his anger.

Goes to abandoned amusement park looking for Saint Johnny or the mysterious man who was previously Darkhawk—no sign of either.

Headset suggests that Chris apply for the internship at RCK Radio. Chris wants to have a better shot at hearing about news fast so that he can help as Darkhawk better. He gets the job.

Peristrike Force is on the move towards Queens on a mission to capture a specialist in superhumans, Professor Vonya, who is speaking at Chris’s high school. 

Chris is playing basketball with friends and amulet hits one in the eye. Couch makes him remove it. Chris puts it in his locker for the time being. The Peristrike Force and agents set up for the assault and kidnapping mission on the school. Mrs Bauer stops Chris at the locker to remind him he’s got to cover the afternoon lecture for the high school station; Chris agrees but makes his way to the ball court first.

The Peristrike Force and agents move in and capture the Russian professor, Anatoly Vonya. Chris discovers the commotion and wants to help but doesn’t have the amulet. He uses his karate to subdue one of the guards on his way to his locker. He frantically tries to open his locker but can’t out of nerves. He gets captured by another guard at gun point who asks for him to open the locker and give him whatever he’s frantically trying to get.
name: Brave New World

description: When The Punisher guest-stars, all bets are off! Two street-level crime fighters vs. The Untouchables, Hardcore’s personal taskforce. Will Cage and Castle bring the thunder? Yes, and then some.
name: Bad Debts

description:
Final Issue! Amanda Waller and what remains of the Suicide Squad face a villain that may be as powerful and cold-hearted as Death itself.

The Squad's quest to stop an island dictator could end in the jungle; all who travel through it are forced to face their deepest fears.

Count Vertigo also faces deep personal emotion problems without the 'assistance' of jungle plants.
name: And Be A Villian

description: What lurks beneath the gleaming spires of Metropolis? Superman finds the ugly and powerful truth in the city's dark underworld. Also, the man who fired Jimmy Olsen is fired himself, and even Perry White is powerless to help him.
name: Panic in the Streets

description:
Classic Judge Dredd reprints from the pages of weekly British anthology comic 2000AD.

Cover: Kev Hopgood (Judge Dredd)

  • Sob Story (part 2 - final part) (prog 132) (John Wagner - Ron Smith)
  • Battle of the Black Atlantic (progs 128-129) (John Wagner - Ron Smith)
  • Who Killed Pug Ugly? (progs 203) (John Wagner and Alan Grant - Ron Smith)
name: Judge Dredd 69

description:
Classic Judge Dredd reprints from the pages of weekly British anthology comic 2000AD.

Cover: Cliff Robinson (Judge Dredd)

  • Heavy Metal Dredd - A Mega-City Primer (Judge Dredd Megazine 1.14) (John Wagner and Alan Grant - Simon Bisley)
  • Bill Bailey, Won't You Please Come Home (progs 723-726) (John Wagner - Vanyo)
name: Dredd Rules! 10

description: Jeremiah Arkham tears down and rebuilds Arkham Asylum and becomes the new Wardon, following in his mad uncle Amadeus' footsteps, however he destroys the diaries of his uncle. In a flashback its shown how Jermiah at 16 started to become interested in twisted minds after witnessed as a fugitive inmate from Arkham shoots himself in the head. As wardon Jeremiah uses brutal methods with the inmates. Batman is incarcerated in the new building. Jeremiah Arkham plans to "cure" him of his Batman persona once and for all.
name: The Last Arkham: Part One

description:
Pantha is put in charge of watching over the extremely strong baby Wildebeest, a task easier said than done.

Pantha has trouble babysitting the newest member of the team.
name: Reflections

description:
Tim Drake prepares for his father's release from the hospital, but with his dad in need of near constant assistance, it just might mean that Batman and Robin might be on their last adventure together.

Tim prepared for his father's release from the hospital. Batman and Robin went out for possibly their last night together (Tim's father would require much assistance and could not live alone). Alfred showed Tim the house nearest to Wayne Manor was for sale.
name: To the Father I Never Knew...

description: "Flash: Year One Born to Run! Chapter 4 - Live Fast...Die Young!" The retelling of the origin of Kid Flash continues as Wally reluctantly heads for home, leaving Iris, Barry, and Central City behind. Once home, Wally rescues his dad from a tornado.
name: Year One part 4: Live Fast Die Young

description:
This issue features four stories.

"Male Bonding - Pt. VIII: Together Forever... a Pair" - starring Wolverine and Nightcrawler

"Against a Rogue God - Part 8: Nauda's Tale" - starring the Young Gods

"Return of the Braineaters - Part 2: Claw and Bone" - In a Brooklyn park, the Ghost Rider attacks the Werewolf, suspecting him as the killer in a series of mutilation murders. They battle, and discover a boy, Billy, who witnessed the Braineaters commit the crimes. Before they can get answers from Billy, he runs away, then the police arrive, forcing the Ghost Rider and the Werewolf to take off as well.

At Billy's home, the Braineaters kill his mother and sister while they await his return. Lupe, a still human member of the gang, begins to have doubts about her place with the rest. Later, in Cypress Hills Cemetery, the Werewolf confronts Dan Ketch.

"I, Thanos - Part One: Into the Abyss" - starring Thanos. [Note: this story takes place during INFINITY WAR #3.]
name: Male Bonding & other stories

description: The 3-part "Blades" storyline begins here! Mr. Lime is killing the elderly in Gotham City, and a frustrated Batman becomes obsessed with bringing him to justice. So, it's up to the swash-buckling Cavalier, Gotham City's newest hero and media darling, to take up the crime-fighting slack.
name: Blades: Part One

description:
The issue opens in a mysterious building in Philadelphia, where the Black Condor's grandfather 
Creighton Kendall reviews surveillance videos of Condor and Ned Smith. Now that he knows where Condor has fled to, he can make arrangements to retrieve him. 
 
However, Crighton does not realize that Black Condor is perched on the top of his building, listening in on their conversation with his enhanced senses. Now that Condor knows the hunt is on, he works on a plan to stay one step ahead of them.
 
Condor is interrupted, however, by Miles Lydecker. Lydecker was once known as the Sky Pirate, and used his hyper-sonic flight technology to rob airplanes in mid-flight. Lydecker has come out of retirement and revived the Sky Pirate identity to confront his arch-enemy, Lawrence Carbo. 
 
Sky Pirate's use of hyper-sonic technology triggers Condor's enhanced senses, causing him pain. Condor tracks down the source of the sonics, and intercepts the Sky Pirate. The two duel in the air above Philadelphia, and Sky Pirate shoots the Condor out of the air, sending him plunging towards the Delaware River.
name: The High And The Mighty

description: Writer D.G. Chichester delivers a script so terrifying, so soul-numbing…it can only come from Hellfire itself! The mercenary Terror begins anew- by tormenting those who cross him.
name: Caveat Emptor

description: Giant sized fun awaits in the lead story, which feature Femforce supporting giantess, Garganta in color in "Island Claws". In an effort to help them both better master their size-changing abilities, Tara Fremont has brought Garganta to the peace and tranquility of her Jungle Island preserve. But the quiet doen't last long, as the island is soon invaded by an even bigger player- that old Lev Gleason anti-hero, ( revived in the AC Universe as a full-fledged super villain) The Claw!! Garganta starts out at fifty feet tall, The Claw even larger ! As the battle of the titans reaches a crescendo, Big G must call on some very special friends to turn the tide. Great giant woman fight scenes and GTS action. Written by Bill Black, drawn by Dick Ayers, and inked by Mark Heike. "Big thrills" continue in the Golden Age section, with a color tale of that redheaded Fiction House babe, Sky Gal(formerly Sky Girl) by Matt Baker- "Crunchy Corn, For The Strength Of A Caveman" reprinted from a story originally appearing in Jumbo.Then, it's more Baker babes in Tiger Girl, from a 1946 issue of Fight Comics., and still a third Matt Baker opus, as he draws his signature character, Fox Feature's Phantom Lady, in glorious color in "The Copy-Cat Killers", originally seen in All Top Comics #14, 1948. Finish with Fran Hopper's Mysta Of The Moon, from Planet Comics #40, a Matt Baker checklist of all his published work, and throw in a Pistol Packin' Pattie ("Belittling") by Frank Bolle, and you've got another book full of sultry, sexy, long-legged girls drawn in the best glamorous, pinup type "good girl art" you can find. Color cover by Bill Black and Mark Heike, interiors are color and black and white with graytones. 52 pages, standard comic book format.
name: Island Claws

description:
Pete and friends struggle to cope with recent events. While Kris takes the loss especially hard, the other renegades try to find the perfect way to honor their friend.

The Harbinger Renegades are still reeling over the death of one of their own. Kris, in particular, is disconsolate over Torque's murder, and she demands that they see to his funeral. So, with Pete's mind-control powers, they steal Torque's body and arrange a quick burial. Each of the kids must handle Torque's death in their own way, but life, and their struggle against Harada, continue.
name: Flowers For The Living

description:
Magnus journeys to the Martian Moon Phobos to deal with the asylum that 1-A created to house the mutated failures in his attempts to generate a robot fighter in “The Asylum Saga Part Two -- Reckonings.”

Magnus arrives at the Asylum on Phobos and meets inmates Izak and Chuh-chuck, who revere him as their ideal hero. However, Grand-One is also there, intent upon eliminating the failed Robot Fighters by flooding the Asylum with poison gas! Forced to battle Grand-One, Magnus kills the very robot that raised him! Saddened by this tragic battle, Magnus decides to look after the inmates, but knows they are too dangerous to set free.

Death of Grand One.

1st appearance:

- Izak
name: The Asylum Saga Part 2: Reckonings

description:
Exiled! As a result of the politics of war Rai is forced to leave Japan with his son. Adrift in space, can Rai make it to Earth?

Exiled from Japan, Rai and his infant son fly to Earth on a shuttle. But a Healer leader has rigged the craft to fly out of control into space! He then assassinates the President and has Kazuyo captured, her ring-hand severed so she cannot summon her armor! Meanwhile, Rai uses the energy in his body to power his shuttle-craft down to Earth. Rising from the wreck with his son, Rai finds Rokkie and Gilad waiting to take him to Unity!

1st appearance:

- Rokland Tate
name: The Infinity Trip

description:
Dark things haunt the nighttime streets of New Orleans, but they only fear one man-- Shadowman! When Jack's housekeeper, Nettie, tells him about the life-sucking Harbinger called Sosa, he vows that this is one monster that won't stalk the night for long.

Crime-lord Emil Sosa has the ability to suck out the life-energy of others, leaving only a burnt-out husk! And now he has his sights on the vigilante -- Shadowman. Capturing the night-roving hero, Sosa locks him in his basement. He is released by a maid, who's had enough of Sosa's perverse appetite for children. But Shadowman doesn't care why he's free, only that he can now eliminate this demon from his night!

1st appearance:

- Sosa (Sousa) the Soul-Eater
name: The Beasts And The Children

description:
Trapped by a force-field, Solar is under attack by the Eggbreakers! But Geoff no longer feels that Solar is the "Sun Demon" he fears will destroy the world. So, as Solar strives not to hurt the misguided Eggbreakers, Gilad convinces Harada to call off the attack. Now, Solar and Geoff go to the home of Erica Pierce, only to find that she has been murdered by her superhuman counterpart from the world Solar destroyed!

1st appearance:

- Jolt

- Quell

- Sponge

- Albert Pierce (1st full appearance)
name: Justifiable Homicides

description:
The showdown with the machine-controlling villain Ax continues, but with his control of the X-O Manowar armor scrambled can Aric still prevail? Aric will show Ax what he does to bandits and Ken what he does to traitors!

As Aric attacks Ax's cyborgs, Ax dons his own alien battle-armor. The ensuing fight leads from air to sea, to an island where Ax's scrambler paralyzes Aric's armor. But he sheds the Good Skin and still bests Ax! Aric spares Ax's life, exchanging him for Ken. But Ken still cannot be trusted, so Aric replaces Ken's severed hand with an extension of an armor that will slay Ken should he ever betray Aric again!
name: Power Play

description: What's the only thing worse than having to face an alien? Doing it AGAIN! And now Ripley's up against them for the third time.
name: 2 (of 3)

description:
Premiering this issue is "Sabotage", a witty tale of war, love, industrial espionage, paranoia and fast cars, by the internationally renowned Daniel Torres! Plus, the second installment of "In Search of Peter Pan", by Cosey ("Voyage to Italy"); more mayhem from Cailleteau and Vatine in "Fred and Bob: The Rabbit Hunt"; and "The Angriest Dog in the World", by David Lynch. Topping it all off is a gorgeous cover painting by Dave Gibbons (Watchmen, Giver Me Liberty)!

Story Titles

  • The Angriest Dog in the World
  • Sabotage Chapter 1
  • In Search of Peter Pan Chapter 2
  • Fred and Bob: The Rabbit Hunt

John Arcudi and Dale Eaglesham's "The Creep" sticks his ugly mug into another case, and Bobby Rubio illustrates a special feature by the group of aspiring writers who attended Steven Grant's writing workshop at last year's San Diego Comic Con. Plus: chapter one of the three-part prequel to the upcoming horror film, Dr. Giggles, by writer/director Manny Coto and artist Alan Burrows!


Chapters

  • Dr. Giggles - Part 1
  • Boris the Bear
  • The Creep
  • "Scraps"
name: Dr. Giggles; Boris the Bear; The Creep; Scraps

description: Overview Bacchus and Simpson travel to Sicily in this first issue of a brand new four-issue series written and drawn by Eddie Campbell. While Bacchus waxes poetic on the Greek god Hephaistus, who set up shop in Sicily back when it was still "The Land of Persephone". Vinnie Bossonova has become a target for Sicily's all-too-modern-day inhabitants-the Mafia! Writer/artist Campbell, illustrator of Alan Moore's From Hell and creator of the outrageous Eyeball Kid as well as the autobiographical Alec stories, puts a novel twist on the characters of Greek mythology (especially the wine-enamored Bacchus). This is the first full-length Bacchus story, and demonstrates his growth as an artist and a storyteller.
name: none

person_credits.name: Eddie Campbell
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

volume.name: Deadface: Earth, Water, Air, and Fire

description: This issue includes two adaptations of Andrew Vachss stories as well a new, previously unpublished short story by Vachss titled "Step on a Crack", with illustrations by Tim Bradstreet. Enemy Ace artist George Pratt adapts "Cripple", and Jerry Prosser (Exquisite Corpse, Aliens: Hive) and James O'Barr (The Crow) adapt "Anytime I Want". Cover painting by James O'Barr.

Part 2 of the 2-part 'The Pursuit of Liberty.' The Sons of Liberty are destroyed...at the hands of their own Agent Liberty!

Notes:

  • First $1.25 issue.
  • Triangle 1992 #27.
  • Chronological continuation from Superman #69.
  • Chronological continuation in Action Comics #679.
name: ...And Justice For All!

description: Animal Man must survive the final passage to achieve his goal as a true animal master. His test is the life destroying Antagon.
name: The Hot Heart of Abstract Reality

character_credits.name: Stone That Cracked Open the Earth Like an Egg

first_appearance_characters.name: Stone That Cracked Open the Earth Like an Egg

description:
Aquaman becomes the target of a deadly assassin and is led on a chase across the rooftops of New York City.

The issue begins with an assassination studying a video tape provided to aid in his assassination of Aquaman,reviewing it in order to make a big splash with his first assassination in America. Meanwhile a recovered Garth lashes out at Aquaman for his choice to bring him to the Idylists for aid,but begins rebuilding his relationship with Garth. Shortly after this Aquaman arrives back to New York where his assassin stalks him in hopes of attacking him following his speech when he becomes weakened from being out of the water.

Aquaman then is forced into a Kevlar vest as he appears before the world's representatives in a effort to gain Poseidonis's entry into the U.N. But following his speech grows angered at the questions asked of him being about his superhero identity and not Poseidonis itself, ending the press conference before storming off,into the rain.

Aquaman then senses his assassin the NKVDemon, and jumps three stories up to confront him. He is then shot, only be saved by the Kevlar vest Mission had insisted he wore, before the Demon set his sights on his unprotected head. However Aquaman is then saved by Batman who drives the villain away, before Aquaman leaves Batman to pursue his attacker. He then finds him and the two engage into hand to hand combat on a New York rooftop, before Aquaman finally defeats him with the police arresting him.

After the battle Batman assumes a disguise to check on Aquaman, while at Rykers Island NKVDemon is murdered in his cell by a prison guard.
name: Demons in Thought & Deed

description:
Maxie Zeus is still running things from inside Arkham Asylum, and his mad assistant is up to something, leaving the Dark Knight to stop her.

Maxie Zeus sent a message to his gang via his girlfriend, Iris. She overheard them discussing their leader in a bad light, but she told them to call off their heist anyway. Iris had a breakdown and became Harpy. She was there to take down the gang when they went on with plans. They escaped when Batman showed up and Harpy went for him instead.
name: Messenger of Zeus
Paved

description: The history of Seaside City's Patriarch is revealed in a bizarre nursery rhyme, "Horton Wears the Hood." Also, the newest Black Hood learns something of the Hood's mysterious power.
name: Horton Wears the Hood!

description: The Comet has disintegrated into nothingness, his costume floating in space...and Rob Connors finally learns the true fate of his missing parents and discovers the true nature of his powers.
name: Burnin' Down the House!

description: In this special double-sized issue, Cliff is paralyzed and the Chief finally reveals the true history of the Doom Patrol. The world's strangest heroes will never recover from these shocking secrets.
name: The Nature of the Catastrophe

description: Eclipso targets Lar Gand, the Creeper and Superman, while the Phantom Stranger delivers a warning in "All Men Make Faults". Continued in Superman: The Man Of Steel Annual #1.
"Fish Story." Wally and Linda Park go on a cruise, and their boat is menaced by sea creatures that are being controlled by the Marine Marauder. Aquaman guest stars.
name: Fish Story

description: An agent of the Web invades the Troy home to learn the connection between young Jason Troy and the Fly, leading to an action-packed confrontation between the agent and the hero...but the Fly doesn't have any idea who he's fighting!
name: Family Matters

description: Hal Jordan returns as the one true Green Lantern of Earth, and just in time to face one of his greatest challenges yet. Evil Star has also returned!
name: Evil Star Rising Part 1: Back in Charge

description:
"Layin' Down the Law" - The story of how Jack T. Chance received a power ring.

"And I shall Shed My Light"- A story about Alan Scott and how he stopped some modern day neo-nazis

"Neither a Lender G'Nort a Borrower Be!' - G'Nort meets his new friend Sax Girl and the two stop the Trio of Greatness from...joining the Justice League?

"What Ever Happened to...Arisia" Continued from JLA #33, fallow Arisia through her mission to find Hal Jordan and figure out who she truly is.

Untitled Story- The sad story about how Shilandra Thane got her power ring.
name: Layin' Down the Law

description: Veteran Green Lantern Ch'p visits the Mosaic world to see how John is trying to keep the various societies together. Unfortunately an evil force is spreading it's influence and Ch'p is run over and killed by a yellow truck.
name: Nuts

description: Escape from Thanagar, Part 4 of 5. Rebel leader Katar Hol presents the rulers of Thanagar with his proposed constitution, while Shayera returns to Earth, sent there by the rulers of Thanagar to keep her from joining the revolutionary cause.
name: Escape From Thanagar! Part 4: Under The Skin; Return of The Voyager; The Wrath of Thanagar

description: Sir Peter Marston is looking to deal with the murderous demon Calibraxis. Constantine must stop him............. by any means neccesary.
name: Royal Blood, Part Four: Dog Eat Dog

description: Jaguar is forced to defend the life of a comedienne who has ridiculed her, while Tracy tries to capture Maria's transformation into the Jaguar on videotape.

Maxima fights for the survival of her homeworld, Almerac, with the help of Superman, Blue Beetle, Booster Gold, Fire, Ice and Bloodwynd...but even the combined might of the Justice League may not be able to stop Starbreaker.
name: The Revenge of Starbreaker

description: It's time for a rebirth as it becomes clear that the mantle of the Shield can no longer be carried by Joe Higgins!

Element Lad Jan Arrah and Shvaughn Erin discover the true nature of their relationship. Meanwhile, in space above the planet, the U.P. Fleet makes a startling discovery.

Due to the Dominators outlawing the drug ProFem, Shvaughn Erin is forced to reveal to the love of her life that she is in fact a man who had been taking gender reassignment pills. Unfazed by the revelation, Jan tells Shvaughn a story to ease her through the pain as she begins her transition back into Sean Erin. Elsewhere, Jan's young SW6 counterpart is having a difficult day of his own as he's faced with the awesome destruction his transmutation powers could cause.
name: Terra Mosiac Part 7

concept_credits.name: With Great Power Comes Great Responsibility

first_appearance_concepts.name: With Great Power Comes Great Responsibility

description: Ms. Tree is nine months pregnant, but that doesn't keep her off the job, nor does it do much to mellow her out. Written by Max Allan Collins, with art by Terry Beatty. Plus, in the back-up tale, King Faraday becomes the target of a mysterious group of assassins while vacationing in Venice. Written by Joey Cavalieri, with art by Carmine Infantino and Frank McLaughlin.
name: Maternity Leave

description:
In the conclusion to this miniseries, Ray is in space, desperately searching to find a way to communicate with a sentient light being about to destroy Earth.

The Ray battles time, space and his own mind to stop the light being and Dr. Polaris. when all is over Ray still has to deal with his adoptive father's death and the broken relationships with his birth father and Jenny Jurden.
name: Day Of The Ray

description: In this single-issue story, a young man becomes lost in The Dreaming where he uncovers wondrous knowledge. The only problem is he might not be able remember it when he awakes...
name: Soft Places

description: In part 5 of the 5-part 'The Road,' Shade discovers what lies in the ditch and the Changing Man must face the ultimate challenge - deciding where to go when there's nowhere left to run!
name: Off the Road, Part Five of Five: The End of the Road

description: Kirk's son returns - it's the resurrection of David Marcus! Kirk, Spock and McCoy investigate a newly discovered planet, where an individual's innermost thoughts are made into a reality that tempts Kirk to abandon the Enterprise!
name: Veritas The Conclusion: Cold Comfort!

description: Part 1 of 3. The enigmatic Q returns to bedevil the Enterprise by playing a practical joke on Picard during a sensitive diplomatic mission, with peculiar consequences for the Klingons.
name: The Way of the Warrior

description: The malevolent Sunderland Corporation returns...and the company's new CEO has vowed vengeance on Swamp Thing. Part 1 of 3.
name: Laissez Les Bon Temps Ruler

description: Silver confronts a past nemesis. Meanwhile, Rothco starts the Posse's training.
Wonder Woman joins Inspector Ed Indelicato in the search for a kidnapped child.
name: The Heart of the City

description: It's Icicle against "The Power of Eraserhead!" plus: Introducing: Madame Sin!
name: Icicle Vs. The Power Of Eraserhead

description: Heroic Publishing's mistress of the occult stars in her first super-sized 44-page issue, by Dennis Mallonee and Duval Stowers. Plus! Witness part 1 of the classic origin of Dark Malice and the original Giant!
name: Bats

description: NOTE: This issue reprints Marvel Two-In-One #77.
name: Only the Swamp Survives

description: An Infinity War crossover.
name: Bare Bones, Part 1

description:
Hera and Ares return to plague the Price of Power Hercules by posessing Thor. When the God of Thunder ravages the Avengers, will Hercules be able to stop the evil at its source and stop Hera and Ares's evil game?

Thuderstrike, Hercules and Crystal go visit a childrens hospital where they are attacked by Hera and Ares. This is the first appearance of Taylor Madison.
name: Death Wager

description:
The search for John Jameson begins! Plus: A werewolf on the hunt! Don’t miss this spooky issue, guest-starring Wolverine.

This issue features two stories.

"The Prowling" - In the woods of Massachusetts, a man is stalked and killed by a werewolf. His body is found the next morning by Wolverine.

At Avengers Headquarters, Captain America works out with the still minimally responsive D-Man. He then talks with Black Widow, asking her to take over as Avengers chairman while he deals with D-Man and the disappearances of his ally Diamondback, and his pilot, John Jameson. Doing detective work, Cap learns of the Moongem that once transformed Jameson into the Man-Wolf, and traces its remnants to the lab of Dr. Curt Connors. There, he talks to Connors' colleague, who discovers the crumbled gem is missing.

Elsewhere, an armored man named Moonhunter is working on taming a group of werewolves in an oubliette when he is summoned by someone he calls "Dredmund".

After a visit to John's father, J. Jonah Jameson, that yields no clues, Captain America takes his sky-cycle to the Boston home of former Avenger Dr. Druid to seek his assistance. Using his affinity for the supernatural, Druid leads Cap to the spot in the woods where the werewolf victim was found. Without warning, a werewolf lunges at them and injures Dr. Druid. Cap, wondering if he might be dealing with a newly lycanthropic John Jameson, holds his own against the beast until it is garroted and snared by Moonhunter from his hover-cycle.

"The Pit and the Pitiful" - Crossbones holds Rachel Leighton (Diamondback) captive in an oubliette in upstate New York in an effort to bend her to her will. Her mind is in a fragile state since a near drowning, and memories of her relationship with Captain America begin to fade.

Elsewhere, Cutthroat sees marks of abuse (delivered by the Red Skull) on Mother Night's face, and expresses his concern with a kiss.
name: Man and Wolf  (Part 1): The Prowling;  The Pit and the Pitiful

description: Rachel Grey's mind is trapped in a coma, so Excalibur turns to the greatest master of the mind on Earth – Charles Xavier!
name: All You Ever Wanted To Know About Phoenix... But Were Afraid To Ask

description: For the first time, the secret origin of the Guardians Of The Galaxy is finally revealed! Was it just a coincidence that the Guardians forged a team or was there another reason? This issue explains how Vance, Charlie, Marty, and Yondu began their personal war with the Badoon.
name: The (Secret) Origin of the Guardians of the Galaxy

description: The Hulk is trying to clean up Las Vegas after the brutal murder of an old friend. A rival Mafia gang is taking over and their power could match the Hulk.
name: Return To Vegas

description:
The evil dopplegangers infiltration of the Marvel heroes has led to mistrust and infighting...and things get worse when a Gamma bomb is detonated!

All the teams have arrived at Four Freedoms Plaza for the meeting called by Mr. Fantastic. They are waiting for a few stragglers before they begin. Doom and Kang are formulating how to find the source of the energy to steal it.

Back on Monster Island, Thanos meets with the Infinity Watch. In order to get information, Thanos has Pip transport them to Death's realm to use the Infinity Well. The Well tells them that when Adam Warlock had the Infinity Gauntlet he subconsciously split the good and evil from himself, thus reviving the Magus. The well informs them that he has great power and plans to assimilate the Earth's heroes with evil copies. But this is all according to the Magus' plan and he informs Death she has trespassers.

Galactus, the Silver Surfer, Nova and Doctor Strange arrive at the energy fluctuation Galactus had picked up. They are able to trace it and head off toward the true source. But Doom and Kang have placed a tracking device on Galactus' ship and plan to follow.

Hawkeye informs Spider-Man of the meeting. When Hawkeye leaves he is attacked by his doppelganger. Spider-Man stops it but is taken out by Iron Man's doppelganger, who now poses as Iron Man.

Reed begins the meeting and tells everyone of the copy that attacked him. Wolverine enters and tells them he was attacked by a copy as well. He also tells everyone that Iron Man and Mr. Fantastic are copies. The heroes become divided and begin to battle before Daredevil also senses they are the true imposters as well. It is revealed that they are both right and the reason Reed wanted them all there before he started was to kill them and a gamma bomb is unveiled.

Thanos and the Infinity Watch learn from Mole Man of the meeting on Earth. Thanos realizes this is no coincidence. They go there just in time to see the gamma bomb explode.
name: Ethereal Revisionism

description: SpectorCorp's being robbed by the Sensor Squad, but Moon Knight appears and takes them out. Later, he is consulting his Shadow Council about the incident and about his next moves. Moon Knight then visits Reed Richards, convincing him to aid with some technology to enter the Latverian Embassy. Marc has one of his Councillors—a girl named Zena who must have a glass eye—pose as a courier to sync Reed's new technology with Doom's systems. That night, Moon Knight enters the Embassy using this tech and despite still finding some safeguards, makes his way to Doom. He battles with Doom, fighting over a locket that belonged to his Doom's Mother. Doom notices that Marc has a "physical condition" that he could help him with in return for the locket. Marc ends up giving him the locket, but refuses his medical help. Back at home, he has second thoughts about this decision as he finds his flesh is falling from his body...
name: Endgame

description:
This issue features four stories.

"Typhoid's Kiss - Part 1: It's Never Over" - starring Wolverine

"Against a Rogue God - Part XI: The Final Conflict" - starring the Young Gods

"Return of the Braineaters - Part 3: Battle on the Brooklyn Bridge" - In Cypress Hills Cemetery, the Werewolf confronts Dan Ketch, then reverts to Jack Russell. Russell tells Ketch about the Braineaters, a murderous motorcycle gang made up of werewolves. Knowing that the boy Billy witnessed two of the Braineaters' murders, Ketch and Russell head for Brooklyn as Ghost Rider and the Werewolf. As the gang closes in on Billy on the Brooklyn Bridge, the two supernatural avengers attack the bikers. The Werewolf takes a motorcycle from one of the Braineaters and rides to try to rescue Billy, but another of the gang hurls a lamppost, jamming the wheel, and vaulting the Werewolf over the side to the river below. The Braineaters then grab Billy.

"I, Thanos - Part Two: Legion of the Doomed" - starring Thanos. [Note: this story takes place during INFINITY WAR #3.]
name: Typhoid's Kiss & other stories

description: Don't miss the exciting conclusion to the biggest Warriors tale yet!
name: Nothing But The Truth, Part 4 - Justifiable Homicide

description:
In the middle of Kree space, Quasar, Makkari, and Her find themselves in front of the gigantic Soul-Eater, unable to communicate with it. The Soul-Eater engulfs them, though Quasar is able to quantum-jump to safety. Back on Earth, Kayla and H.D. head out for a much-needed vacation only to be waylaid by Quagmire, who has recently been broken out of prison. In the Kree galaxy, Quasar attempts to attack the Soul-Eater with his quantum power, to no effect other than to frustrate Quasar even further. Epoch explains to Quasar the origin and nature of the Soul-Eater, summarizing the events of Thor 261-263. The Soul-Eater is a psionic energy being empowered by the life force of others. Once it was a celestial being in a symbiotic existence with a race known as the Deonists, though this being was destroyed by a war, forcing the Deonists to power the Soul-Eater (and their own protection) another way: the life force of Odin. Thor and his cohorts rescued Odin from the Soul-Eater construct. A Deonist named K'rll altered the structure of the Soul-Eater, turning it into its present form of a life-energy siphon, destroying the Deonist race in the process. Now the Soul-Eater travels the cosmos searching for new souls to increase its own power and existence. It has stolen the souls of the billions of Kree recently killed by the Nega-Bomb during Operation: Galactic Storm.

Armed with this knowledge, Quasar fights it in earnest, only to be reminded his quantum energy is ineffective against it. The Soul-Eater escapes after another meal, but Quasar is able to track it down, thanks to Epoch. Its next meal is a small organic space embryo. Quasar, repulsed at the Soul-Eater's careless disregard for young life, renews his assault by attacking it from the inside. Despite his enthusiasm, Quasar has little success against the Soul-Eater, hampered in part by his musings over his authority to destroy a unique life-form, considering he opposed the "renegade Avengers" and their assassination of the Supreme Intelligence. Not even the omnipotent Epoch has any suggestions on how to defeat it.

Soon, the souls of the Kree come to Quasar, wondering why he is in their afterlife. He explains they aren't really dead but are being kept in a kind of limbo state until the Soul-Eater finishes digesting them, preventing them from ever getting to it. Though some are not interested in helping Quasar help them, others heed what he says about the dignity they have earned in their death, a dignity which is being forestalled by the Soul-Eater. Moments later, the Soul-Eater explodes from the inside out - apparently the Kree souls heeded Quasar's plea for dignity. Quasar rescues Makkari and Her, admitting he had nothing to do with the final destruction of the Soul-Eater. Quasar gives a moment of silence for the finally-dead Kree, pondering the irony of his attempts to assist the living but actually assisting the dead become truly dead, an unusual task for the Protector of the Universe.
name: Soul Cage

description:
Silver Surfer visits Titan to see Nebula. Nebula is in a catatonic state since Starfox tried to take away her suffering. The Surfer goes to visit Mentor who is down in the tombs since it is the anniversary of his wife's death at the hands of his son, Thanos. He tells Surfer the true story of her gruesome death. They are interrupted when they learn that Galactus has returned to Earth.

The Surfer rushes to Earth to find Galactus abducting Doctor Strange. The Surfer will not allow this and follows to Galactus' ship. Galactus forces Nova to attack the Surfer and she must do her duty. The battle is stopped by Doctor Strange when he awakens. He tells the Surfer that he is willingly helping Galactus and it would be wise for the Surfer to help as well. All reality is in peril from the being known as Magus.
name: Sins Of The Fathers
Riot on Ryker's Island!

description:
To protect the Drake family, Iceman and Hiro battle the Cyburai!

Ice Man fights to save the lives of his parents. What will be Storm's answer to Forge's proposal? Mystique reaches a turning point in her life. And, more is revealed about Peter's mysterious brother, Mikhail.
name: Frayed

description: A confused Spider-Man wakes to find that Maxie Shiffman is his agent and he's in the middle of making a Hollywood movie involving Galactus and the X-Men.

What if the Watcher Saved the Multiverse

description: Introducing Hell’s Belles! X-Factor must take down a terrorist cell comprised of female mutants. What do Hell’s Belles want from X-Factor? And will the team be able to save a Belle-gone-good before her fellow teammates retaliate?
name: Belles & Whistles

description:
After a brief battle, Gideon sends Crule to attack X-Force and bring in the newest External, Cannonball. Weapon Prime prepares to battle X-Force. Cable plans to use the fake Domino to infiltrate Tolliver's base and take him out for good.

Synopsis

In Madripoor, a huge, purple brute takes out a cantina when he suspects cheating in a card game. He is Crule. He is also who Gideon has come to see. The two have a strained relationship, at best, and begin a knock-down, drag-out fight. Gideon, however, is able to mimic the powers of other mutants and soon gets the upper hand due to his technique. Once Crule has settled down he asks what is needed. Gideon states that a man needs to be stopped - Cable.

In the X-Force base, the team surrounds who they think is Domino and ask how she could betray them (they having found her pretty battered after their excursion to the Morlock Tunnels, coupled with the supposed accounts of Shatterstar and Siryn about Deadpool's infiltration). She simply states that she is a mercenary and the money from Tolliver was good. Besides, after how Cable left his former team, the money would help to pay for certain operations. Shatterstar wants to kill her immediately; Cable has other plans.

Weapon: PRIME is about ready to be placed in action, they just need one more component. Grizzly gladly joins the ranks. G.W. Bridge then lays out the plan: everyone fights until they can't, then the SHIELD ship they travel dishes out all it can. The goal is to take Cable down one way or another. The team is told to rest up for a very eventful day.

"Domino" places a call to Tolliver. She informs him that Deadpool's visit has reminded her of her true mission and she plans on blowing up the X-Force base while the team is in a scheduled practice session. Tolliver is pleased and promises a pardon for her past behavior if all goes to plan. After the call is over, Cable expounds the rest of his plan. Now that Tolliver knows that the base is going to explode he won't expect an attack by the X-Force team that he thinks will be dead. Cable moves out to prepare his team for evacuation.

On the Weapon: PRIME ship, Kane runs into Rictor. Rictor is far from sleep and tells Kane that he is also more than ready to take on Cable. Years ago, he states, he watched Cable kill his father. Kane's resolve to get Cable deepens.

Gideon and Crule land at Gideon's corporate offices. Sunspot is surprised that such a brutal looking mutant would be brought in as an associate. Gideon begins to act short with Sunspot now that he knows that Sunspot is not the ascending High Lord that he had originally thought (that supposedly being Cannonball). Sunspot asks one too many questions and Gideon unloads on the boy, pummeling him into unconsciousness. Gideon then tells Crule that there are plans for Sunspot.

In the X-Force base, Cable breaks the news that the team must vacate. The base will be allowed to be destroyed so that no one can have access to information about the team. Also, he has grown tired of the looming Tolliver threat and plans to use X-Force to end it once and for all. The team preps to leave.

Just outside the base, Weapon: PRIME prepares to strike.
name: Traitors to the Cause

description: Wolverine is stuck in a situation that could be the end not only the team, but the world!
name: Where Happy Little Bluebirds Fly... / Last Stand

description:
It's an all-out melee for our group of heroes in Japan! Who will walk away unscathed, and who will be changed forever? Answers: no one, and everyone!

After driving off Cylla with Sunfire's aid, Wolverine and Gambit seek help from Mariko in finding Jubilee. Arriving at his fiance's home, Wolverine finds the Silver Samurai attempting to wrest control of the Yashida Clan while Matsuo and Silver Fox, with Reiko as their pawn, converge on them to settle their grudges. Jubilee is accompanied by Yukio as they make their way to Wolverine.
name: We Got Cylla, Can Mothra Be Far Behind?

description: "Blades" continues as Batman saves an aging film star from the explosive wrath of Mr. Lime, but is unable to catch the elusive killer. The Cavalier is far more successful as Gotham City's new crime-fighter, cutting a swath through the city's underworld.
name: Blades: Part 2
